glimmer /ˈɡlɪmə/

(glimmering,glimmered,glimmers) 

1. V-I If something glimmers , it produces or reflects a faint, gentle, often unsteady light. 闪烁微光 

例： The moon glimmered faintly through the mists. 月亮透过薄雾闪烁着微光。 

2. N-COUNT A glimmer is a faint, gentle, often unsteady light. 微光 

例： In the east there is the slightest glimmer of light. 东方有一丝闪烁的微光。 

3. N-COUNT A glimmer of something is a faint sign of it. 一丝 (迹象) 

例： Despite an occasional glimmer of hope, this campaign has not produced any results. 尽管偶尔有一线希望，这次宣传活动并没有产生任何结果。

